Description:
    Bilingual (Portuguese/English) interactive Shiny application for systematic
    and scoping review support. Imports records from PubMed, Web of Science,
    Scopus, and custom sources; performs automatic deduplication; calculates
    composite relevance scores (thematic and bibliometric components);
    classifies articles into priority tiers (P1-P4); generates bibliometric
    networks with Louvain clustering; and exports a structured Excel workbook
    with PRISMA flow data, annotation templates, and auto-generated methods
    text in both languages. Recency scoring is relative to the user-defined
    search date; the Louvain clustering seed is user-configurable for full
    reproducibility. Cross-platform file navigation detects all available
    system drives automatically.
